      <item>
        <title>Frontity lightbox for wp content images</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[grimurnet]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Just wanted to put it here in case someone else is looking for a similar solution.</p>
<ol>
<li>Install the package</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">npm install --save simple-react-lightbox
</code></pre>
<ol start="2">
<li>add the following line to post.js</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">import SimpleReactLightbox, { SRLWrapper } from 'simple-react-lightbox'
</code></pre>
<ol start="3">
<li>add the following around </li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">&lt;SimpleReactLightbox&gt;
  &lt;SRLWrapper&gt;
   &lt;Html2React html={post.content} /&gt;
  &lt;/SRLWrapper&gt;
&lt;/SimpleReactLightbox&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>That should be enough, you can also style it to your liking.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/frontity-lightbox-for-wp-content-images/5221/4">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
